In England, in the seven days to 24 September, there were 186,637 new confirmed cases (330.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 September, there were 146,249 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 28% (40,388 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 29 September is 6,617,892 (11,702.7 cases per 100,000 population).
